The files module
================

This module handles files
	>>> import files

		It can show    spaces and	tabs
		
and ends of lines

	>>> files.looks_like_this(test.path,[5,10])
	 5: 	>>> import files
	 6: 
	 7: 		It can show    spaces and	tabs
	 8: 		
	 9: and ends of lines
	10: 

	>>> files.looks_like_this(test.path,[5,10],space='.',tab='|...',sol='^',eol='$',numbers=False)
	^|...>>>.import.files$
	^$
	^|...|...It.can.show....spaces.and|...tabs$
	^|...|...$
	^and.ends.of.lines$
	^$

Write some failing tests to a file
	>>> import doctests
	>>> doctests.write_failing_test('made_earlier.test')

Which looks like this )default is that line numbers start at 1)
	>>> files.looks_like_this('made_earlier.test')
	 1: Test Me
	 2: =======
	 3: 	>>> print 1
	 4: 	>>> print 2
	 5: 	3
	 6: 	>>> print 1 / 0
	 7: 	>>> print 0

Run that test through doctest to generate some failures
	>>> doctests.try_to_pass_tests('made_earlier.test')
	False

